1. destructor is an instance member function of class which is used to release the resource of the object.
2. when our object is destroyed our destructor is called .
3. destructor has no return type and you can not pass anything in destructor and it is declared with tield sign before writing its name.
4. It is going to invoked implicitly when object is going to destroy.
5. destructor can never be static.
6.Overloading is not possible.
7. destructor is made by compiler ownself if we didnot made it.
8.IT SHOULD BE DEFINED TO RELEASE RESOURCES ALLOCATED TO AN OBJECT.
